Subject: What Lies Beneath the Waters
Description: Have you ever wanted to be a treasure hunter? Join us for an introduction to finding treasures and fossils hidden beneath rivers and streams!  Speakers include:Patrick Allen, Mary Fitzpatrick - Track: Science  - Duration: 1 hour

Subject: Knitting 101
Description: Learn to knit! Take two sticks and string and make a dishcloth! Supplies provided.  Speakers include:Mary Fitzpatrick, Kelly Vanderwell - Track: DIY  - Duration: 1 hour

Subject: Double Knitting
Description: Double it up in this panel as we teach you how to make things on both sides of the skein. Basic knit and purl stitch skills required to bring double the trouble in this panel!  Speakers include:Mary Fitzpatrick, Patt Mundy - Track: DIY  - Duration: 1 hour

Subject: Incorporating STEM in the Classroom
Description: Join us for a discussion about how to get kids excited about tech and STEM!  Speakers include:Frannie, Mary Fitzpatrick - Track: Science  - Duration: 1 hour
